condition.narrative: Finance Agreement: Schedule 2 Section IA1 | Description :Maintain, at all times, during implementation the IRCBP Technical Steeringcommittee, chaired by the FS of MoFED, with mandate, composition and resources satisfactory to the World Bank. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2 Section IA2 | Description :Maintain, at all times, the Technical Coordinating Committee forReproductive and Child Health, chaired by the CMO of MoHS with mandate, composition and resources satisfactory to the World Bank. |Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2 Section IA3 | Description :Maintain, at all times, the Integrated Project Administration Unit withinMoFED with TORs acceptable to the Association, staffed with qualified and experienced personnel in adequate numbers. | Frequency:Yearly

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2 Section IB1(i) | Description : Adopt a manual outlining implementation, organizational, admin, M & E,environment and social monitoring and mitigation, financial management, disbursement & procurement arrangements for project | DueDate :30-Sep-2010

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2 Section IB1(ii) | Description :Prepare and adopt a PBF Operational Manual with maximum aggregateamount for each year, list of PBF subprojects and unit costs for each service and maximum % to be financed under each subproject. |Due Date :17-Jun-2011
Finance Agreement: Schedule 2 Section IB1(iii) | Description :The Recipient shall prepare and adopt a form of PBF Services GrantAgreement. | Due Date :06-May-2011

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2 Section IB2 | Description :Recipient shall enter into MOU with Njala University and University ofSierra Leone, setting forth modalities for cooperation and coordination in the implementation of Part 2(b) of the Project. | DueDate :31-Dec-2010

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2 Section IB3 | Description :The Recipient shall prepare and furnish WB for approval a proposed workplan/ budget for all proposed activities for following Fiscal Year specifying sources of funds and % of financing | Frequency:Yearly

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2 Section IC | Description :The Recipient shall ensure that the Project is carried out in accordancewith the provisions of the Anti-Corruption Guidelines. | Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement: Schedule 2 Section ID | Description :The Recipient shall ensure that the Project is carried out in accordancewith the provisions of the ESMF. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2 Section IE1 | Description :In order for a Subproject to be eligible for financing under an LC Grant,it shall be required to satisfy conditions elaborated in the GA and OM. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2 Section IE2a | Description :The Recipient shall make each LC Grant on a non-reimbursable grant basisto the LC concerned under a Subsidiary Agreement acceptable to WB, include terms and conditions in GA and OM. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2 Section IF1 | Description :Recipient shall review and approve applications for PBF Services Grants inaccordance with the provisions of GA Part F and the PBF OM. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2 Section IF2 | Description :The Recipient shall determine that proposed Beneficiaries and PBF ServicesSubproject satisfy eligibility criteria specified in the GA and elaborated in the PBF OM before financing. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2 Section IIA1 | Description :Recipient shall monitor and evaluate Project progress, prepare ProjectReports based on agreed indicators, submit to WB for each calendar quarter not later than 45 days after period. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2 Section IIB1-3 | Description :Recipient shall ensure: 1) maintain financial management system; 2)interim unaudited financial reports furnished to WB not later than 45 days after quarter; 3) audited financial statement to WB. |Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2 Section IIIA1 | Description :All goods, works and services required for the project and to befinanced out of the proceeds of the Grant shall be procured in accordance with requirements of IBRD/IDA Procurement Guidelines. |Frequency :Yearly
